	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I stand corrected on the cause (which was just a guess anyway).
<br />
<br />As for how far you have to go to save... I'd say it takes 5-10 minutes on a totally fresh file. However, if you have an existing save and start a new game, you can hit Start to skip the initial cutscenes, then head up, avoiding most of the plants' attacks, then die at the boss on the next screen, at which point you will be dragged to a save point where you can save in another slot.
<br />
<br />From there, a soft reset is enough to see that the save in the new slot is corrupted.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
